<br>
Also, the spawn time is different between them. With FG's there is an 8hr spawn time. With IG's it is what? Half hour or an hour? Part of training with FG's is you do not get a back-spawn. Same goes with Hate and Fear. You also do not want to throw in a back spawn when someone is doing their first Multi-Group Raid. They have enough issues to worry about with out that. You gotta crawl before you can walk.<br>
<br>
Also, distance for the level of raid FG's fall into IS a problem to try to replace it with IG's. Reason is the zones one must go through to get there. First you need a port to NK, then you need to run through one of the longest zones in the Old World. Then, if you are a Dark Race, you have wandering MoBs in QH that run at faster than SoW speeds, and they are not slackers by any measure of the word. Then, in Everfrost, you have the same thing to contend with or at least a simulair situation. And before you say &quot;well, just invis and SoW&quot; remember how far from dense civilization that area is. Black Burrow is a low level dungeon. I seriously doubt you could get an invis there on a normal day. Also, Skellies wander around at the Everfrost side of BB. One incidental whack from them and there goes your invis.<br>
<br>
When I run into Fear I do not invis even tho Da Basha probably can still clean my clock. But, with a SoW that lasts from NFP all the way to the SS and the fact he is generally avoidable, who cares? As I stated earlier, this is not the situation in QH or Everfrost to Dark Races. <br>
<br>
Before you say &quot;There are gaurds that the light races have to deal with to get to FG's&quot; let's compair those gaurds. In Nek I was killing gaurds SOLO at 12. By my upper 30's I could take down the wandering Dragoon solo. DE's cannot outrun SoW. The two Eco-terrorists in QH are souped-up 30's. The Gaurds are aroung 40. In Everfrost the gaurds are again around 40 with a couple of wanderers that are 47 to 50.<br>
<br>
Also, in Fear and, I think, in Hate, one does not have to deal with pit traps like one would in Permafrost, pit traps with level 50 monsters at the bottom of them. Also, in Permafrost most of the IG's are pulled to the King Room and delt with there. One does not have the oppertunity to train in moving multi-groups to several different staging areas nor does one have the opportunity to train groups on how to move MoBs away from objects. The Pillers in Tranx's room are like trees in Fear or walls in Hate. I lost my first piece of Valorium to a tree in Fear and have seen a near total wipe out in Hate due to wall agro.<br>
<br>
And, I can see the arguement creaping in that the Pit Traps are like Wall Agro in Hate creaping in. The fact is that the Perma death traps are NOT the same as a TT might knock someone into a pit. Not having the firepower to take down a Dragon would make such a CR very diffacult and perhaps expensive.<br>
<br>
So, in conclusion, the travel to Permafrost is not compairable to travel to Fear or Hate, especially for Dark Races. Also, the training oppertunities between the FG's and IG's are uncompairable. And, finally, what is wrong with dangling loot in front of appropriat levels' eyes to get up the numbers needed to make up the multiple groups that are needed for raid leaders to train in multigroup raid leadership? That comes to the age old question of &quot;what if someone decided to declair war but no one showed up for it?&quot;<br>
<br>
