<br>
my math might be bad but lets see .... that means 40 more reservations can be added to the list .... when we add rage fire / fire giants raids in the next two weeks we are down to ....  38 unreserved spawns .... <br>
<br>
<br>
it takes about an hour or less to get a raid going that had signups and was reserved...<br>
<br>
how long does it take to get 2 or 3 high lvl people together to go kill fire giants? a port to lava and zone in ... about 5 minutes?<br>
<br>
my question to everyone that wants fire giants not reservable<br>
<br>
why?<br>
<br>
it is not the fire giants reservations that are holding you up ...at getting rage fire. you can track ragefire with a ranger and then go kill him if he is up. ( I am sure any legitamate fire giant raid will not get too upset) I would be the first to congrat the cleric.<br>
<br>
if the high lvl people are upset because they cant farm the giants because of reservations. well you say you only need 2 or so people to kill them why is it so hard for you to form a group and go kill them the other 35+ chances you get in a 2 week period?<br>
<br>
only problem I see here is greed(or should I say the need to get an item before anyone else) is getting in the way of clerics working out a comprimise between themselves and greed from farmers cause they have to upgrade their porches or make the rent this month.<br>
<br>
I am not trying to flame anyone or anything I am just stating my opinions and my thoughts about this situation.<br>
<br>
call me crazy but I dont see a problem with reserving fire giants so you feel a little better about their chances of being there when you get your 18 to 24 members of a party together.<br>
<br>
oh btw I pay 10 bucks a month just like the rest of you.<br>
I just dont see how having the fire giants unresevable will help anyone? I can see how it helps the 35th to 50th level crowd. <br>
<br>
get a ranger track rage fire guy and when he spawns get your crew together (get then together fast if rage is first come first serve) and have at it. and good luck.<br>
<br>
<br>
